256
00:16:42,315 --> 00:16:44,442
As if I could ever forget her...

257
00:16:46,110 --> 00:16:47,820
Where are you?

258
00:16:48,863 --> 00:16:50,364
What are you doing?

259
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,075
Nakamura...

260
00:16:53,159 --> 00:16:55,202
[laughing]

261
00:17:00,624 --> 00:17:02,543
-[splatters]
-Oh.

262
00:17:04,962 --> 00:17:06,088
[groaning]

263
00:17:06,172 --> 00:17:09,425
Hey! How dare you knock over
Mr. Tetsu's bowl of oden.

264
00:17:10,301 --> 00:17:13,637
I'm sorry. Let me pay for it... please.

265
00:17:13,721 --> 00:17:14,847
Pay for it?

266
00:17:14,930 --> 00:17:16,766
You think that's gonna be enough?

267
00:17:16,849 --> 00:17:19,894
Do you know what
Mr. Tetsu's shirataki noodles are worth?

268
00:17:19,977 --> 00:17:22,104
-His shirataki noodles!
-[Tetsu] Calm down, now.

269
00:17:22,605 --> 00:17:25,691
[chuckles] I'm not a monster.

270
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:28,944
Why don't we go have a chat over there?

271
00:17:35,076 --> 00:17:36,827
All right, then.

272
00:17:37,495 --> 00:17:40,373
Give me all the money you got.

273
00:17:40,456 --> 00:17:41,457
[Takao] What?

274
00:17:42,083 --> 00:17:43,876
But...

275
00:17:43,959 --> 00:17:46,712
I'm really disappointed
that I couldn't eat my shirataki.

276
00:17:47,213 --> 00:17:49,298
That was the last one in the store.

277
00:17:49,382 --> 00:17:50,883
It's the least you can do.

278
00:17:52,218 --> 00:17:53,386
[Takao] No...

279
00:17:56,889 --> 00:17:58,307
[groaning]

280
00:18:02,978 --> 00:18:04,939
Mr. Tetsu is saying he'll forgive you.

281
00:18:05,022 --> 00:18:06,941
-So, get your money out.
-[breathing heavily]

282
00:18:08,442 --> 00:18:10,903
[Takao grunting] Wait!

283
00:18:16,117 --> 00:18:18,160
[chuckles, inhales]

284
00:18:18,911 --> 00:18:21,789
-[coins jingling]
-[exclaims]

285
00:18:21,872 --> 00:18:23,541
That's it?

286
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,252
How sad is that?

287
00:18:26,335 --> 00:18:29,839
[exclaims] Great arm. [chuckles]

288
00:18:29,922 --> 00:18:31,090
Let's go.

289
00:18:31,882 --> 00:18:33,843
Life must be fun for you two.

290
00:18:34,802 --> 00:18:35,970
[Tetsu] What was that?

291
00:18:38,305 --> 00:18:40,850
You obviously have no doubts
about your lives...

292
00:18:41,809 --> 00:18:44,437
[breath trembling] It must be nice.

293
00:18:44,979 --> 00:18:47,064
[♪ melancholy music playing]

294
00:18:47,148 --> 00:18:48,983
-Hey.
-Sure.

295
00:18:53,404 --> 00:18:54,822
[groaning]

296
00:18:58,784 --> 00:19:00,244
[yelps]

297
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:08,669
-[Tetsu chuckles]
-[goon] Watch your mouth, kid.

298
00:19:15,342 --> 00:19:16,802
You see...

299
00:19:18,095 --> 00:19:20,181
I died that day.

300
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:23,350
I lost everything.

301
00:19:25,644 --> 00:19:27,938
And yet, here I am.

302
00:19:28,981 --> 00:19:31,358
Alive and shamefully breathing.

303
00:19:33,861 --> 00:19:35,237
[breathing shakily]

304
00:19:35,321 --> 00:19:36,947
I'm practically a zombie.

305
00:19:37,448 --> 00:19:38,741
A zombie, you see...

306
00:19:38,824 --> 00:19:40,159
What's your deal?

307
00:19:40,242 --> 00:19:41,994
Mumbling creepy shit.

308
00:19:43,662 --> 00:19:44,747
[Takao grunts]

309
00:19:53,005 --> 00:19:54,965
[breathing heavily]

310
00:19:55,049 --> 00:19:56,133
Hey...

311
00:19:57,802 --> 00:19:59,637
tell me, would you?

312
00:20:01,555 --> 00:20:03,933
How should I live on?

313
00:20:04,975 --> 00:20:08,354
How can I be like you,
living so shamelessly?

314
00:20:09,396 --> 00:20:10,397
Tell me...

315
00:20:11,315 --> 00:20:13,150
shit bugs.

316
00:20:17,071 --> 00:20:18,739
[groaning]

317
00:20:20,407 --> 00:20:21,534
[coughing]
STYLE
::cue()

318
00:20:23,410 --> 00:20:25,162
[screaming]

319
00:20:25,246 --> 00:20:27,790
[Tetsu] That hurts, doesn't it?

320
00:20:32,795 --> 00:20:35,089
What's with your obnoxious talking?

321
00:20:36,173 --> 00:20:39,552
If you're gonna bother people,
go kill yourself already.

322
00:20:40,135 --> 00:20:41,220
You piece of shit.

323
00:20:43,138 --> 00:20:44,557
[Takao grunting]

324
00:20:47,017 --> 00:20:48,727
-[Tetsu] Let's go.
-[goon] Sure.

325
00:20:49,228 --> 00:20:50,563
[Tetsu] I'm kinda hungry.

326
00:20:50,646 --> 00:20:51,939
[goon] Yeah, I'm hungry, too.

327
00:20:52,022 --> 00:20:53,190
[Tetsu] Wanna get some gyudon?

328
00:20:53,274 --> 00:20:55,526
[goon] Gyudon? Great idea.

329
00:20:55,609 --> 00:20:57,278
[Tetsu] I want one with shirataki noodles.

330
00:20:57,361 --> 00:20:59,363
-[goon] We'll find one with lots of 'em.
-Yeah.

331
00:20:59,446 --> 00:21:01,282
[Takao breathing shakily]

332
00:21:04,243 --> 00:21:05,536
[Takao grunts]

333
00:21:12,543 --> 00:21:13,586
[groans]

334
00:21:21,385 --> 00:21:22,720
He's right.

335
00:21:24,805 --> 00:21:26,348
I suppose...

336
00:21:27,016 --> 00:21:29,184
I'd be better off dead.

337
00:21:43,782 --> 00:21:45,409
[sighs]

338
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:05,804
WE BUY OLD BOOKS - MIYAMA BOOKSTORE

339
00:22:09,058 --> 00:22:10,517
Books...

340
00:22:11,685 --> 00:22:12,978
Like they'd do any good now.

341
00:22:26,158 --> 00:22:30,037
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

342
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:31,956
-[♪ rock music playing]
-[gasps]

343
00:22:40,464 --> 00:22:42,007
[gasps]

344
00:22:48,555 --> 00:22:50,891
TO BE CONTINUED

345
00:22:50,975 --> 00:22:53,060
[♪ closing theme music playing]

346
00:23:48,032 --> 00:23:49,074
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

347
00:23:49,158 --> 00:23:52,745
[narrator] Kasuga sees a resemblance
between Tokiwa and a girl he once knew.

348
00:23:52,828 --> 00:23:56,665
But that small moment of joy
is brutally torn apart.

349
00:23:56,749 --> 00:23:58,834
Next, on episode nine,

350
00:23:58,917 --> 00:24:01,879
What is Tokiwa's secret
that only Kasuga knows?

351
00:24:01,962 --> 00:24:02,963
Translated by Yuka Kristi

